parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster lighting can cause the gauges, speedometer, and other essential information to be unreadable at night, posing a significant safety risk to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The lights in the gauge cluster go out or dim
making it difficult or impossible to read the gauges
and other essential information at night

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Evaporative Emission Control (EVAP) Canister Fuel Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak from the EVAP canister can cause fuel to spill onto the rear passenger wheel fender liner, creating a fire hazard, especially when driving under heavy loads or cornering. This can lead to vehicle fires, potentially resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the EVAP canister
fuel stains around the EVAP canister
strong fuel fumes inside the cabin
fuel overflow after filling the tank.
